						<summary>

						<p>Slab built into the Vīrasangayya-kaṭṭe.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Bhuvanaikamalla [Sōmēśvara II] 1070 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>The epigraph is engraved on four faces of a slab of which the bottom portion is broken and lost. It seems to register a gift to a <hi rend="italic">basadi</hi> constructed by Paḍavaḷa Chāvuṇḍamayya, a disciple of Śubhachandra-siddhāntadēva. Paṁpa-permānaḍi, by a subordinate of the king Chālukya Śrī-Bhuvanaikamalla (Sōmēśvara II).</p>						

						<p>It is dated Śaka 991, Saumya, Phā(lguṇa) and the rest of the information is lost. The given details correspond to 1070 A.D., February-March.</p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
